The introduction of a new German warship was again postponed
The most modern frigate of the German Navy was to be put into operation in 2014 instead of outdated Cold War fighting vessels. However, according to local media information, this will not happen until at least next year due to faulty systems and rapid increase in costs.
According to the newspaper Die Zeit, received from the spokesman of the military department, the commissioning of the ship "Rainland-Pfaltz", the main vessel of the series of the most modern frigates of the class "Baden-Wurtemberg", is postponed until the first half of 2019.
